OL,4,Cwater on disabled friend
OL,6,FBanks, of The Friary, Nottingham,
OL,7,Freceived a 10-year sentence and
OL,8,FTurner, of Hazelwood Road, got eight
OL,9,Fyears.
OL,11,FDetective Constable Jack Beecroft, of
OL,12,F, said: "This was an appalling attack
OL,13,Fon a disabled woman who could not
OL,14,Fdefend herself.
OL,16,F"It is difficult to imagine the pain
OL,17,Fand terror she must have experienced
OL,18,Fwhen this full kettle of boiling water
OL,19,Fwas poured on her, and she was
OL,20,Fattacked by people she knew.
